Movie: Black Mirror: Rachel, Jack and Ashley Too

Review: A good story doesn’t require you watch it on a big screen! As much as I regret not watching this in the theaters, I enjoyed watching in an airplane and I was hooked on! There is something slick about Darren’s  visual storytelling that in fact from the first frame of the film I knew I am going to like it! I am not an easy person to cry but I was in tears!
